description: LALIGA Power is a program that pays tribute to all those who inspire the world through the values of football. In each episode, we discover the passion celebrities have for their club and experience a match day with the most dedicated fans in the world, as well as showing curiosities about LALIGA clubs and players. Because they are the strength of our football.

title: Real Madrid vs Mallorca - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 36
description: Real Madrid have won 12 of their last 13 home games against Mallorca in LaLiga, following a run of four winless home games against the Balearic team in the competition. After a 1-1 draw at Son Moix in August 2024, Mallorca can pick up points in both of their LaLiga games against Real Madrid in the same season for the fourth time in history, having previously achieved it in 1989/90, 2000/01, and 2001/02.

title: Real Valladolid vs Girona - LaLiga 2024/25 Week 36
description: Real Valladolid have won both of their home matches against Girona in LaLiga, both 1-0. Only against three teams have the Valladolid side won their first three home matches without conceding in the top-flight: Mallorca in 1983, Cádiz in 1986, and Alaves in 1998. After their victory in the reverse fixture in December 2024, Girona can win back-to-back matches against Real Valladolid in all competitions for the second time in history, having achieved this feat between 2015 and 2016 in LaLiga Hypermotion.

title: Stadium of Fears

Several big names in football tell you about their experiences in these stadiums where it can sometimes be difficult to play.

title: Mainz 05 vs Bayer Leverkusen - Bundesliga 2024/25 Week 34
description: 1. FSV Mainz 05 have lost 11 of their 14 Bundesliga games against Bayer 04 Leverkusen since the start of 2018 – the Werkself haven’t beaten any other side more often during this period and the 05ers haven’t suffered more defeats against any other side. Leverkusen have won each of the last three meetings. Bayer 04 Leverkusen have only won one of their last five Bundesliga games. 68 points from 33 games is still their third-best record in the top flight. Last weekend’s 4-2 defeat against Borussia Dortmund saw them concede more than three goals in a Bundesliga game for the first time since October 2022.

description: Episode three of The World Chess Show looks at some of the hot topics in chess at the moment and asks whether the growth of the game online and the shorter formats threaten the classical format. VfL Wolfsburg are winless in their last nine Bundesliga games, the longest ongoing wait in the league and the Wolves’ longest spell without victory since between December 2023 and March 2024.
